# Cancel Token Rules

Use `ApiCancelToken` (`core/api/models/api_cancel_token.dart`) for any request that is slow, large, or user-interruptible: search queries, file uploads/downloads, paginated fetches, map/media data.

## Data source
Add `ApiCancelToken? cancelToken` as a named optional parameter and forward it to `ApiClient`:

```dart
// ✅ GOOD
Future<List<RouteModel>> searchRoutes(String query, {ApiCancelToken? cancelToken}) async {
  final response = await _apiClient.get(
    ApiConstants.routes,
    queryParameters: {'q': query},
    cancelToken: cancelToken,
  );
  return (response.data as List).map((e) => RouteModel.fromJson(e)).toList();
}
```

## Repository interface
Declare the same optional parameter so domain can pass a token when it needs control:

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — domain/repository/routes_repository.dart
abstract interface class RoutesRepository {
  FutureEither<List<Route>> searchRoutes(String query, {ApiCancelToken? cancelToken});
}
```

## Repository implementation — cancellation is silent
When cancelled, `ApiClient` throws `ApiException(type: ApiExceptionType.cancel)`.
Check for it **before** `toFailure()` and return `Failure.api(type: FailureType.silent, ...)`.
`FailureType.silent` tells the BLoC to reset quietly — no error UI is shown.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD
@override
FutureEither<List<Route>> searchRoutes(String query, {ApiCancelToken? cancelToken}) async {
  try {
    final models = await _remote.searchRoutes(query, cancelToken: cancelToken);
    return Right(models.map((m) => m.toEntity()).toList());
  } on Exception catch (e) {
    if (e is ApiException && e.type == ApiExceptionType.cancel) {
      return Left(Failure.api(type: FailureType.silent, source: '$runtimeType'));
    }
    return Left(e.toFailure(source: '$runtimeType'));
  }
}

// ❌ BAD — cancellation becomes a snackbar error
} on Exception catch (e) {
  return Left(e.toFailure(source: '$runtimeType'));
}
```

## UseCase Params
Include `ApiCancelToken?` in the `Params` class — nullable, so callers that don't need it pass `null`:

```dart
class SearchRoutesParams {
  const SearchRoutesParams({required this.query, this.cancelToken});
  final String query;
  final ApiCancelToken? cancelToken;
}
```

## BLoC — own the token, cancel on close

The **BLoC owns `ApiCancelToken` as a private field** — never put it in Freezed state.
Override `close()` to cancel when the screen is dismissed.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD
class RoutesSearchBloc extends Bloc<RoutesSearchEvent, RoutesSearchState> {
  final SearchRoutesUseCase _searchUseCase;
  ApiCancelToken? _cancelToken; // BLoC field — NOT in Freezed state

  RoutesSearchBloc(this._searchUseCase) : super(const RoutesSearchState()) {
    on<RoutesSearchQueryChanged>(_onQueryChanged, transformer: restartable());
  }

  Future<void> _onQueryChanged(RoutesSearchQueryChanged event, Emitter<RoutesSearchState> emit) async {
    _cancelToken?.cancel();          // cancel previous in-flight request
    _cancelToken = ApiCancelToken(); // fresh token for this request

    emit(state.copyWith(status: StateStatus.loading()));
    final result = await _searchUseCase(
      SearchRoutesParams(query: event.query, cancelToken: _cancelToken),
    );
    result.fold(
      (failure) {
        if (failure.type == FailureType.silent) {
          emit(state.copyWith(status: StateStatus.initial()));
          return;
        }
        emit(state.copyWith(status: StateStatus.error(failure)));
      },
      (routes) => emit(state.copyWith(status: StateStatus.success(), routes: routes)),
    );
  }

  @override
  Future<void> close() {
    _cancelToken?.cancel('bloc closed'); // fires when screen is popped from the stack
    return super.close();
  }
}

// ❌ BAD — token in Freezed state
const factory SearchState({ApiCancelToken? cancelToken}) = _SearchState; // ❌

// ❌ BAD — no close() override; request keeps running after screen dismissal

// ❌ BAD — cancellation shown as error
result.fold((failure) => emit(state.copyWith(failure: failure)), ...); // snackbar on cancel
```

## Rules summary
- `_cancelToken` is a **BLoC field**, never inside Freezed state
- Cancel the previous token at the **start** of every new request
- Always override `close()` — this is the screen-dismissal hook
- `restartable()` stops event processing but does **not** cancel the HTTP request — you still need the token
- On fold: `FailureType.silent` → emit `StateStatus.initial()`, do not show any UI
